message: I think she stated this in an interview, though 935866418 by [[Special:Contributions/Tdc42|Tdc42]] ([[User talk:Tdc42|talk]])

I am certain James Barbagallo won the bronze medal. He and his thrid prize achievement at the International Tchaikovsky Competition are displayed at the alumni wall of distinction at Juilliard (where I attended). Here is a reliable link in addition to the one cited previously: https://www.nytimes.com/1996/03/01/nyregion/james-barbagallo-us-pianist-43-who-won-prizes.html

Many Wikipedia biographies contain information similar to this in their personal life sections so I don't see why it hurts to add it here. Also it doesn't seem like private information in any way and 3 people have helped edit this -- just leave it in.
